des:
SystechSmart skill helps you control thousands of smart devices from a single platform. You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or off your plug, switch, gadgets, home alliances, and curtains, etc.
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your plug, switch, gadgets, home appliances, and curtain - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
Connect Alexa to your SystechSmart products in a few simple steps:

1. Download our "SystechSmart" all-in-one app in the Android or iOS app store;
2. Register one SystechSmart account in our "SystechSmart" all-in-one app;
3. You need to have some Smart devices in hand by SystechSmart;
4. Configure these devices in our "SystechSmart" app and change the appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Systech Smart Solutions" skills;
5. Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Android, iOS, or Amazon app market;
6. Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
7. Search "Systech Smart Solutions" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
8. Click Enable skill of "Systech Smart Solutions", and you'll be navigated to the "Systech Smart Solutions" login page;
9. Input your SystechSmart account username and password, you'll be redirected to the success page;
10. Now all setup is finished

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
"Alexa, turn on Fan to 60%."
"Alexa, turn off Fan"
"Alexa, turn on Dimmer to 80%."
"Alexa, turn off Dimmer"
"Alexa, turn on Coffee Maker."
"Alexa, turn off Coffee Maker."
"Alexa, open the Curtain to 60%."
"Alexa, close the Curtain."
